content: Project Apollo scope and key deliverables were finalized. Task ownership assigned. Follow-up on server security (Task 12) needed.
The team chose a path for the navigation algorithm, prioritizing stability over initial performance. External library integration is the next step.
Action plan created to research and develop solar-capture improvements. Budget allocation review scheduled.
Agile Scrum was adopted for Delta project development. Training is mandatory for all team members.
The AI model selection process concluded with a decision to use both LSTM and Transformer models for different prediction horizons.
Testing protocols for the biotech product were finalized, with an emphasis on a larger sample size requirement.
The team is proceeding to prototype production for the AI-optimized golf equipment based on positive feedback.
A migration strategy to PostgreSQL was approved. The target completion is Q4, pending detailed backup plan finalization.
The schedule for the infrastructure upgrade was set to occur only during weekend low-traffic hours.
MFA implementation was identified as the highest priority security enhancement.
